Package gui

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    RefreshListener
    listener that tells an object how to refresh/update
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Boundary
    Boundaries are rectangular shapes, ellipses and actual rectangles drawn on the screen when the user is setting up their chamber configuration.
    Configurations
    Configurations provides static methods for obtaining and saving user preferences.
    DrawingTool
    A Mouse and Key Listener, allows users to draw ellipses and rectangles on a canvar, and label them as either sources, sinks, or walls.
    EditLattice
    Opens a specified image to its fullest size possible according to screen dimensions in a separate JFrame from the ILB.
    LatticePanel  
    LBMGui
    Opens the application and defines the main window.
    Main
    Launch and run the ILB
    MessageBar
    The Message bar is a simple panel with a progress bar for showing the loading status of the current background thread, and a JLabel for relevant errors that users might like to know, like if FaceMatch didn't load
